column47: I think that the choices could have included one more middle choice of say average.
I may have rated the first selection too high, but I thought all of the governors showed a total positive result for their terms, I thought they all did good or great.
It was an interesting survey. Good basis for measuring the effect of term limits.
I would present less graphs, they all start looking very similar
Thank You for giving me the chance to participate in your survey!
I'm unsure how long a governor's term is for. Is it 4 years? I put in 16 years for the last question assuming this, but I'm unsure if it's 2 years for governors.

Frequently governors have little influence or control   on how well business does during their terms.  The current economic situation in the United States is a good example of how larger trends can affect the individual state economies.
